OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1775661069
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 13 Apr to Wed 22 AprFIt
OL,6,Fwill likely remain rather changeable
OL,7,Fduring the first part of this period,
OL,8,Fwith showers or occasional longer
OL,9,Fspells of rain interspersed with drier
OL,10,Finterludes. The pattern will likely
OL,11,Fbecome increasingly slow evolving,
OL,12,Fwith low pressure to the northwest of
OL,13,Fthe UK and high pressure over
OL,14,FScandinavia. This may lead to more in
OL,15,Fthe way of drier, settled weather,
OL,16,Fespecially in the north and east,
OL,17,Falthough there will still be showery
OL,18,Foutbreaks, particularly in the south.
OL,19,FWhen the winds are light, it should
OL,20,Ffeel quite warm, despite temperatures
OL,21,Fmost likely being close to normal for
OL,22,Fmost.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
